==English==

{{rank|light|felt|since|250|use|used|began|thy}}

===Pronunciation 1===
*yo͞os, /juːs/, /<tt>ju:s</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-use-noun.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-uːs|Rhymes: -uːs]]

====Noun====
'''use''' (''countable and uncountable; plural:'' '''[[uses]]''')

#(''countable'') The act of using.
#:''The '''use''' of torture has been condemned by the United Nations.''
#:''There is no '''use''' for your invention.''
#(''uncountable; followed by'' '''of''') [[usefulness|Usefulness]], [[benefit]].
#:''What's the '''use''' of a law that nobody abides to?''
#A [[function]]; a purpose for which something may be employed. 
#:This tool has many '''use'''s.

====Synonyms====
*(''act of using''): [[employment]], [[usage]]
*(''usefulness''): [[benefit]], [[good]], [[point]], [[usefulness]], [[utility]]

